07/25/2025,748.3441(a) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,08/04/2025,08/08/2025,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium High,Yes,During the walkthrough of the kitchen multiple dry and wet food items were expired and multiple food items were not stored properly.,"Supervisor conducted a physical follow-up at the operation and a full walkthrough was conducted. Supervisor inspected the kitchen checking both dry and wet foods and no concerns with the expiration dates nor food storage were observed.  It was observed that the operation adds the received date on their foods items, which is different from the expiration date, and this is not a concern nor risk to children as none of food items were expired nor spoiled.  Supervisor also observed all refrigerators/freezers to be accurately reading at the time of the inspection. Supervisor reviewed the opening-closing checklist and interviewed the staff regarding the new process that the operation has implemented, and no concerns were noted.  Staff uses FoodSafety.org to ensure they are following the correct protocols and staff has access to the website at all times and it's reviewed to ensure they are correctly following the chart based on the food storage."
